This paper deals with the development of efficient distributed communication protocols in multi-hop ad hoc networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and their time complexity, which is a topic in the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of formal frameworks and models for analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with the development of efficient and scalable solutions, which is a topic in the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
